text=https://i.imgur.com/7OlUpfb.png%0a(:include GameRef.Directoryhelp:)%0a----%0a%25center%25https://i.imgur.com/0f53Cck.png%0a----%0a[[#top]]%0a(:toc:)%0a%0a'+%25center%25'''Wanton Wicked 6 (WW6) is a 2nd Edition (2E) Game.'''+'%0a\\%0a\\%0aBecause new books for 2nd Edition are still being published, this list will be updated throughout the duration of 6.0. The books listed below are all the currently approved books in use.%0a%0a!!%25center%25'''Available to Players'''%0aUnless otherwise noted, all non-optional mechanics in these books are available to players.%0a%0a*World of Darkness 2E: The God Machine Rules Update (available for free)%0a**Bygones are available, but must be earned IC, and generally go through Custom Item approval.%0a*Chronicles of Darkness%0a*2E Core Books:%0a**Vampire: the Requiem 2E (a.k.a. Blood and Smoke: The Strix Chronicles)%0a***The [[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1zXoidmr88S_my76fkV-ITr27wHSdtVdeFMfcpXMkhY4/edit#|FAQ]] is in use.%0a**Beast: the Primordial%0a**Changeling: the Lost 2E%0a**Werewolf: the Forsaken 2E%0a**Geist: the Sin-Eater 2E %0a***Sin-Eater characters are not available yet, but see the cross-venue merit policy below.%0a*Supplements:%0a**BtP: Player’s Guide%0a**CoD: Dark Eras%0a***Anything that isn’t noted specifically as not existing in modern times, is 2nd edition mechanics, is meant for a gameline that we allow PCs in, and that doesn’t have a prerequisite that’s specific to an era, can be taken. For instance, Contract with the Uncanny (a covenant merit) cannot; it requires status in a non-existent Covenant. Changeling mechanics from the “old” system cannot be used (but see [[CustomItemsAndPowers]] for any conversions).%0a***'''Skin Thief''' is treated as a "micro template"%0a**CoD: Dark Eras Companion%0a***As above.%0a**CoD: Dark Eras 2%0a***As above.%0a**CoD: Hurt Locker%0a***See [[Character Creation]] for rules on what Merit Templates can be taken.%0a**VtR: Secrets of the Covenants%0a**VtR: Spilled Blood%0a***Chapter 1 is available to players, but the Jharana are not available at this time%0a***Chapter 2 is currently not available to players; if you want to develop a similar ability, talk to the Rulesmaster and Storymasters. Things that become available through plot or other public development will be listed here%0a***Chapter 3 is storyteller use only%0a**VtR: Thousand Years of Night%0a***See [[House Rules]] for clarifications on Elder prerequisites%0a**VtR: Half-Damned%0a***Dhampir are playable. '''Guru Ghouls are not currently playable'''.%0a**VtR: Guide to the Night%0a***Nothing relying on Lingua Bellum or alternative settings may be taken. Colonies and Coterie merits are fine, as are general merits and Devotions.%0a**WtF: The Pack%0a***See [[House Rules]] for rules on what mechanics can be used by Packs.%0a**WtF: Shunned by the Moon%0a***Pure Gifts can be taken as non-affinity.%0a***Healing Old Wounds (rite) can be taken. %0a***See below for Supernatural Merits.%0a***Everything else in the book is Storyteller use only.%0a%0a*Storytellers Vault: Note that at this time, we’re not considering new additions to this list.%0a**BtP: Mother’s Magic%0a**CofD: Ephemeral Influence%0a**CofD: Second Sight: Third Eye%0a***Chapter Three is Storyteller use only%0a**VtR: Bloodlines: the Resurrected %0a**VtR: Devotion to Power%0a%0a%0a!!!%25center%25''Restricted to Staff/Approved PRP Use Only''%0a**All cores and supplements of unused venues (Mage, Demon, Promethean, etc)%0a***This also means that PC’s should not attempt to take Allies, Mentors, Contacts, or similar merits related to character types that are not approved for play. History involving them is fine, so long as they have no current access to them. %0a**BtP: Night Horrors: Conquering Heroes%0a**BtP: Building a Legend%0a%25right%25[[#top | &#8593; back to top]]%0a%0a!!%25center%25'''Cross-Venue Merit Policy'''%0aSome books contain merits that are appropriate for those of other character types, and for the sake of player convenience they’ve been listed here with their appropriate sources.%0a*'''Note that any prerequisites listed must still be met.'''%0a*''An * by the merit means that it always requires Justification, or a background explanation at creation.''%0a*A ^ means not available at creation, but can be gained ICly.%0a**Both only apply to those outside of the given book’s faction (So, a Changeling can buy Hedge Sense at creation with no issue, for instance).%0a%0aFinally, '''no merit listed grants access to template abilities, unique merits (other than those listed here), or powers of other Factions'''; Chorister won’t let a Werewolf learn Cruac, for instance.%0a%0a!!!%25center%25''Can be taken by anyone''%0a*''‘Mundane/Human’'' section merits in all books ('''NOT''' human-only merits), including non-Supernatural merits in the Chronicles of Darkness line.%0a*Supernatural Item merits, if gained from another character or a plot^*%0a**Does '''not''' provide any special ability to '''USE''' them.%0a*Ceremonies (see Geist)*, except Krewe related ones, are buyable as merits. %0a*Architect (GtS pg 85)%0a*Casual User (SotC pg 178)^*%0a*Chorister (SotC pg 181)^*%0a*Empowered to Speak (VtR pg 300)*%0a**''Must be Blood-Bound''%0a*Expressive (CtL 319)%0a*Independent Study (SotC pg 193)^*%0a*Killer Instinct (BtP pg 117)%0a*Laity (SotC pg 193)^*%0a*Library, Advanced (BtP pg 117)%0a*Manic States (GtS pg 86)%0a*One Foot in the Door (SotC pg 187)^*%0a*Reconciler (GtS pg 87)%0a*Relentless Assault (BtP pg 118)%0a*Residential Area (WtF pg 107)%0a*Retribution (GtS pg 88)%0a%0a!!!%25center%25''Can be taken by non-templated/micro-template Mortals''%0a*Any non-template Supernatural Merit%0a*Any merit with "Human" as the prerequisite%0a*Clear-Sighted (VtR pg 299)%0a**'''This counts as a Supernatural merit.'''%0a*Herd (VtR) can be taken by Psychic Vampires specifically. It provides Ephemera instead of Vitae.%0a*Shadow Occultism (SbtM 138)*%0a**Shadow Occultists count as a “Micro Template”%0a*Shadow Perception (SbtM 138)*%0a%0a!!!%25center%25''Can be taken by any Half-Templates'':%0a*Beast Whispers (VtR pg 300)%0a*Beloved (VtR pg 300)^*%0a*Protected (VtR pg 299)*%0a*Weakened Bond (VtR pg 299)%0a%0a!!!%25center%25''Can be taken by any Supernatural''%0a*Totem (WtF pg 108)%0a**''ONLY if in a Pack with a Werewolf, and only 1 dot without Magnanimous Totem''%0a*Dedicated Locus (WtF pg 106)*%0a*Faerie Favor (CtL pg 114)^*%0a*Grave Goods (GtS pg 86)*%0a%0a
