diff:1572732386:1546995096:=9c9%0a%3c '+%25center%25'''Wanton Wicked 6 (WW6) is a 2nd Edition (2E) Game.'''+'%0a---%0a> '+%25center%25'''Wanton Wicked 5 (WW5) is a 2nd Edition (2E) Game.'''+'%0a12,13c12,13%0a%3c Because new books for 2nd Edition are still being published, this list will be updated throughout the duration of 6.0. The books listed below are all the currently approved books in use.%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Because new books for 2nd Edition are %25red%25''still being published''%25silver%25, this list will be updated throughout the duration of 5.0. The books listed below are all the released and scoped books for 2015/2016. With the exception of Changeling (See Caveat below), only officially published book material is allowed.%0a> %0a18d17%0a%3c **Bygones are available, but must be earned IC, and generally go through Custom Item approval.%0a23,24c22,23%0a%3c **Beast: the Primordial%0a%3c **Changeling: the Lost 2E%0a---%0a> **%25red%25Changeling: the Lost 2E%0a> **Mage: the Awakening 2E%0a26,27d24%0a%3c **Geist: the Sin-Eater 2E %0a%3c ***Sin-Eater characters are not available yet, but see the cross-venue merit policy below.%0a29d25%0a%3c **BtP: Player’s Guide%0a31c27%0a%3c ***Anything that isn’t noted specifically as not existing in modern times, is 2nd edition mechanics, and that doesn’t have a prerequisite that’s specific to an era, can be taken. For instance, Contract with the Uncanny (a covenant merit) cannot, since it requires status in a non-existent Covenant. Changeling mechanics from the “old” system cannot be used (but see [[CustomItemsAndPowers]] for any conversions)%0a---%0a> ***Anything that isn’t noted specifically as not existing in modern times, is 2nd edition mechanics, and that doesn’t have a prerequisite that’s specific to an era, can be taken. For instance, Contract of Abjuration is allowed, it’s just out of affinity, but Contract with the Uncanny (a covenant merit) cannot, since it requires status in a non-existent Covenant.%0a34,36c30%0a%3c *CoD: Hurt Locker%0a%3c **See Character Creation for rules on what Minor Templates can be taken.%0a%3c *VtR: Secrets of the Covenants%0a---%0a> *VtR: Secrets of the Covenants (With ST Approval)%0a40c34%0a%3c **Dhampir are playable. '''Guru Ghouls are not currently playable'''.%0a---%0a> **Dhampir are playable. '''Guru Ghouls are not currently playable'''. %0a42c36,39%0a%3c **Nothing relying on Lingua Bellum or alternative settings may be taken. Colonies and Coterie merits are fine, as are general merits and Devotions.%0a---%0a> **Nothing relying on Lingua Bellum or alternative settings may be taken. Colonies and Coterie merits are fine, as are general merits and devotions.%0a> **Note also that Tutelage can only be used to be a student ''or'' teacher, not both each story.%0a> *WoD: Hurt Locker%0a> **See Character Creation for rules on what Minor Templates can be taken.%0a44,59c41,47%0a%3c **See [[House Rules]] for rules on what mechanics can be used by Packs.%0a%3c *WtF: Shunned by the Moon%0a%3c **Pure Gifts can be taken as non-affinity.%0a%3c **Healing Old Wounds (rite) can be taken. %0a%3c **See below for Supernatural Merits.%0a%3c **Everything else in the book is Storyteller use only.%0a%3c %0a%3c *Storytellers Vault: Note that at this time, we’re not considering new additions to this list.%0a%3c **BtP: Mother’s Magic%0a%3c **CofD: Ephemeral Influence%0a%3c **CofD: Second Sight: Third Eye%0a%3c ***Chapter Three is Storyteller use only%0a%3c **VtR: Bloodlines: the Resurrected %0a%3c **VtR: Devotion to Power%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a---%0a> **See House Rules for rules on what mechanics can be used by Packs.%0a> %0a> !!%25center%25'''Changeling Caveat'''%0a> When approaching WW5, because The Onyx Path is producing a new system of books (Chronicles of Darkness aka 2E), we had made it a policy to only produce games where a published book is available to all players and staff. The Onyx Path anticipates publishing the rules for Changeling: the Lost 2E this fall, but there is always a chance for delay. However, because of the popularity of the Changeling venue and the anticipation of this publication date, we have decided to launch the Changeling venue with the advanced preview of the character creation rules that The Onyx Path has provided.%0a> \\%0a> For this reason, we wanted to also notify our potential Changeling players of a rather major Caveat Emptor (Buyer Beware): When the book is published there may be changes to elements of character creation (for example, kith or seeming effects, changeling merits, fae-touched merits, etc.) If this is the case, your character will be modified to reflect the official, published rules. ''There will be no grandfathering''.%0a> %0a61,64c49,56%0a%3c **All cores and supplements of unused venues (Mage, Demon, Promethean, etc)%0a%3c ***This also means that PC’s should not attempt to take Allies, Mentors, Contacts, or similar merits related to character types that are not approved for play. History involving them is fine, so long as they have no current access to them. %0a%3c **BtP: Night Horrors: Conquering Heroes%0a%3c **BtP: Building a Legend%0a---%0a> *2E Core Books:%0a> **Beast: the Primordial%0a> **Demon: The Descent%0a> **Promethean: the Created 2E%0a> **Hunter: Mortal Remains%0a> *Supplements:%0a> **DtD: Flowers of Hell%0a> **DtD: Heirs to Hell%0a69,71c61,65%0a%3c *'''Note that any prerequisites listed must still be met.'''%0a%3c *''An * by the merit means that it always requires Justification, or a background explanation at creation.''%0a%3c *A ^ means not available at creation, but can be gained ICly.%0a---%0a> \\%0a> %0a> *'''Note that any prerequisites listed must still be met.''' %0a> *''An * by the merit means that it always requires Justification, or a background explanation at creation.'' %0a> *A ^ means not available at creation, but can be gained ICly. %0a74,75c68,70%0a%3c Finally, '''no merit listed grants access to template abilities, unique merits (other than those listed here), or powers of other Factions'''; Goodwill doesn’t let a Vampire learn Court Contracts and Chorister won’t let a Werewolf learn Cruac, for instance.%0a%3c %0a---%0a> \\%0a> Finally, '''no merit listed grants access to template abilities, unique merits (other than those listed here), or powers of other Factions'''; Order Status won’t let a Vampire learn Rotes, Goodwill doesn’t let a Mage learn Court Contracts or Goblin Vow, and Chorister won’t let a Werewolf learn Cruac, for instance.%0a> %0a80,85c75,85%0a%3c *Ceremonies (see Geist)*, except Krewe related ones, are buyable as merits. %0a%3c *Architect (GtS pg 85)%0a%3c *Casual User (SotC pg 178)^*%0a%3c *Chorister (SotC pg 181)^*%0a%3c *Court Goodwill (CtL pg 112)^*%0a%3c *Empowered to Speak (VtR pg 300)*%0a---%0a> *Sleepwalker merits (MtA pgs 305–306)%0a> **''Except for Mages and non-Sleepwalker mortals''%0a> *Astral Adept (MtA pg 100)^*%0a> **''If a Sleepwalker''%0a> *Destiny (MtA pg 100)*%0a> **WP is needed for any supernatural power, not just spellcasting%0a> *Order Status (MtA pg 100)^*%0a> **''1 dot cap for non-Mages, and only if not a Sleeper''%0a> *Infamous Mentor (MtA pg 102)*%0a> **Relies on and affects a faction-relevant status type%0a> *Empowered to Speak (VtR pg 300) *%0a87,94d86%0a%3c *Independent Study (SotC pg 193)^*%0a%3c *Killer Instinct (BtP pg 117)%0a%3c *Laity (SotC pg 193)^*%0a%3c *Library, Advanced (BtP pg 117)%0a%3c *Manic States (GtS pg 86)%0a%3c *One Foot in the Door (SotC pg 187)^*%0a%3c *Reconciler (GtS pg 87)%0a%3c *Relentless Assault (BtP pg 118)%0a96,97c88,99%0a%3c *Retribution (GtS pg 88)%0a%3c %0a---%0a> *Court Goodwill (CtL Playtest)^*%0a> **Limited to 2 dots for non-changelings%0a> *Diviner (CtL Playtest)%0a> *Lucid Dreamer (CtL Playtest)*%0a> *Prophet (CtL Playtest)%0a> *Warded Dreams (CtL Playtest)%0a> *Casual User (SotC pg 178)^*%0a> *Chorister (SotC pg 181)^*%0a> *One Foot in the Door (SotC pg 187)^*%0a> *Laity (SotC pg 193)^*%0a> *Independent Study (SotC pg 193)^*%0a> %0a99,100c101,1